<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112/3475</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Rio de Janeiro</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GALM1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gottschalk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-12T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your April 10, 6 p.m. You may inform Lloyd Brazileiro Department knows of
                            no legal obstacle to the transaction to which they refer. Point out,
                            however, that this statement of Department is, of course, made in
                            contemplation of existing conditions only.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>